{"session_id":"svc-1781927719814105700","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-20T03:55:19.861693934Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet-4.6","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude-tui","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet-4.6","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-8e54a916-20260620T035457-ea654273","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child/sibling/replacement bead.\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add` only for legitimate child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges; never the parent.\u0026#xA;3. Use `Parent=\u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` as hierarchy metadata; do not add the decomposed parent as a dependency.\u0026#xA;4. After a lossless durable split, close the decomposed parent with `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;` once child/sibling/replacement beads are filed. Otherwise, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under `bundle` with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Don\u0026#39;t mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; don\u0026#39;t parallelize `git add`, `git commit`, or staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; subject ends with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, or `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`. Step 0 allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add` for child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges, and `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;- If a verification command is auto-backgrounded by the harness, wait for its completion before rerunning the same command in the same worktree.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-8e54a916\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eFEAT-028: define BlobStore interface in cli/internal/blob/ + migrate attachments \u0026amp; execution evidence\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;FEAT-028 (Storage Abstractions, Status: In Progress, P1) names the BlobStore interface as the \u0026#34;first concrete deliverable,\u0026#34; but no implementation exists.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-028-storage-abstractions.md:71-89 (\u0026#34;In Scope (v1)\u0026#34;) mandates a new cli/internal/blob/ package defining a BlobStore interface, plus migration of two call-site clusters behind it. The package cli/internal/blob/ does not exist (verified: \u0026#39;ls cli/internal/blob\u0026#39; -\u0026gt; ENOENT). Externalized bead attachments still write directly via cli/internal/bead/attachments.go, and per-attempt execution evidence still writes directly via cli/internal/agent/execute_bead*.go under .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;run-id\u0026gt;/. No open bead tracks this work (2026-06-19 doc/impl alignment audit).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Create cli/internal/blob/ with the BlobStore interface (methods, error semantics, key conventions, content-addressed vs caller-keyed — exactly as decided in FEAT-028 In-Scope v1), provide LocalFSBlob and MemoryBlob implementations, and migrate (1) externalized bead attachments (attachments.go) and (2) per-attempt execution-evidence writers behind it.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;cli/internal/agent/executions_mirror.go stays direct-FS (StreamStore, deferred). Do not migrate cli/internal/registry/. No GC/quota. Do not define EntityStore/StreamStore/ConfigStore (follow-up beads).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEP NOTE: no deps; orthogonal to the axon Backend epic (TD-027) which abstracts the bead store, not blob state.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/blob/blob.go defines a BlobStore interface with documented error semantics and key conventions matching FEAT-028 In-Scope v1.\u0026#xA;2. LocalFSBlob and MemoryBlob implementations exist with a shared TestBlobStoreConformance covering both.\u0026#xA;3. cli/internal/bead/attachments.go writes externalized attachments through BlobStore; existing attachment tests stay green.\u0026#xA;4. Per-attempt execution-evidence writers in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead*.go route through BlobStore; on-disk .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;run-id\u0026gt;/ layout unchanged.\u0026#xA;5. cli/internal/agent/executions_mirror.go is unchanged (direct FS) with a comment citing the FEAT-028 StreamStore deferral.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/blob/... ./internal/bead/... ./internal/agent/... green.\u0026#xA;7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:build, area:storage, kind:feature, spec:FEAT-028\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"dcc17935929a4db5f9f29105ea3a72ce02518cb2\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260620T035457-ea654273\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior 